laboratory_examinations.findings: The appendix is abnormally dilated with a proximal diameter of 14 mm. The appendiceal tip tapers to a diameter of 10 mm. There is extensive wall enhancement and surrounding fluid and phlegmonous change. A small periappendiceal fluid collection is seen measuring approximately 2.1 x 2.8 x 2.4 cm. Multiple small lymph nodes are seen in the RLQ, likely reactive. A small amount of free fluid is seen in the pelvis.
